[Today's update is optimistic as there was only one newly confirmed case of MERS-CoV infection reported in the past 24 hours. There was also one new fatality reported, in an individual who was reported as newly confirmed yesterday (17 Jun 2015).

Hopefully this is an indicator that the control measures implemented are impacting and slowing down transmission. Fortunately another "super spreader" has not appeared, and contacts with other cases are fewer and spread around rather than all focused on a few select cases.

An indicator of the massive efforts on the part of the MOH is the volume of contacts being monitored in quarantine... today's total is 5930 as 12 percent decrease from yesterday's (17 Jun 2015) when there were 6629 individuals under quarantine.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of South Korea can be found at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3447481,195. - Mod.MPP]

