1035 laboratory-confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection, including
458 deaths,
571 recoveries, and
6 currently active cases

In the past 24 hours there have been:
0 newly confirmed cases,
0 newly reported fatalities, and
1 newly reported recovery

[The case fatality rate remains at 44.3 percent]

Information on newly reported recovery:
A 50-year-old expat male, healthcare worker (HCW) from Hufoof with no history of pre-existing disease [was initially reported as a laboratory-confirmed case on 3 Jun 2015, at which time he was noted to be in stable condition. At the time of initial report, he had a positive history of contact with another case in either the healthcare environment or in the community -- as he is a HCW, his contact was most likely in the healthcare environment as there has been the ongoing outbreak in a hospital(?s) in Hufoof. - Mod.MPP]

